Before we can think about what we need for our server and  network, we need to understand what our requirements are in terms of:

  1. Network data types
  2. Server-only data types
  3. Data volumes
  4. Redundant disks
  5. ZFS Special devices

So please buckle up whilst we take you on a guided tour of NAS “Requirements Specification” or as Uncle Fester would call it “Wha'd'ya want?”
